22 Section 56 of the Judiciary Act , on which Mr Croker relied, provides as follows:
'(1) A person making a claim against the Commonwealth, whether in contract or in tort, may in respect of the claim bring a suit against the Commonwealth: (a) in the High Court;
(b) if the claim arose in a State or Territory--in the Supreme Court of that State or Territory or in any other court of competent jurisdiction of that State or Territory; or (c) if the claim did not arise in a State or Territory--in the Supreme Court of any State or Territory or in any other court of competent jurisdiction of any State or Territory.
